+1 
Issue reproduced using Android Studio Bumblebee | 2021.1.1 Patch 1 and Android Studio Bumblebee | 2021.1.1 Patch 2
Alongside flutter_windows_2.10.0-stable and flutter_windows_2.10.2-stable
It happened to me today. I debugged code yesterday and everything worked as it should. After upgrading the flutter plugin this morning it stopped working.
I've solved the problem.we need to roll back the version of the flutter plugin to 64.1.2.

+1
How do you downgrade the flutter plugin ?
https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/9212-flutter/versions
+1 Seeing this as well. Solution was to revert back to the latest v64.x release.

I see two people who have reported this problem are using Windows. I can't reproduce it using my Mac.

Is anyone who sees this problem using either the Linux or Mac versions of Android Studio?
How to revert the flutter plugin? Where to place the files?

Download the appropriate version for your IDE to a local file. In Android Studio open Settings and select Plugins. There's a gear icon in the right-hand pane, at the top. Click it, then choose "Install Plugin from Disk..." and select the file you just downloaded.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19659454/156472056-2de52f83-a0cb-4edb-bea4-a9d81c11bae8.png)

BTW, I'm still trying to determine if this problem is specific to Windows. If everyone would include the output from 
```dart
flutter doctor -v
```
that would really help.
